  "text": "1) Structure of Cosface Face Recognition Model: Cosface's sphere20 network are shown in Fig. 7 . The pre-trained model parameters of the feature extraction part which is outside the dotted box in Fig. 7 have been given. The parameters of the classifier part which is inside the dotted box in Fig. 7 have to be retrained. The pre-trained model parameters of the face feature extraction part are imported and frozen during training process. This part does not participate in backpropagation. Only the parameters of the classifier are updated in backpropagation. 452,960 face images from 10,575 individuals in CASIA-WebFace dataset are cropped by Multi-task Cascaded Convolutional Networks (MTCNN, a face detection and calibration framework) [CITATION_1] to the size of 112×96 and then are used as the training set. Batchsize is set to 100. The gradient descent algorithm is SGD. Learning rate is initially set to 0.1 and gradually reduced to 0.0000001. After 6 epochs of training, we obtained a pre-trained model of the classifier of the Cosface network.",
